                     <interp inst="t16840702-6-person26" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             came and desired his Wife to go out with him, under pretence to go see a Cousin that dwelt on the Fields-side; that his Wife<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="16840702002"></xptr>was unwilling to go, saying she had not Cloaths good enough to go a Visiting: but he alledging his Cousin was to go into the Country the next Day, and that he was not ashamed of her Cloaths, she at length Consented, and borrowed a Hood, and a Scarf, of this Fellow-Servant 
               <persName id="t16840702-6-person27">
                  Sarah 
                  Miller
               <interp inst="t16840702-6-person27" type="surname" value="Miller"></interp>
